<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#707070"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Sevok Celith'ar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Have any fellow Necromancers found a secret to getting our pets to be better tanks?  <P>Any combination of buffs - be it from Enchanter, Shaman, Druid, or whatever class is needed - that will cause them to actually be able to keep MOBs on them, rather than on, say, a bard or rogue that is duoed with you?<P>They have Taunt, supposedly, but I've never seen a case where it worked.  Even if I have to pay 20pp to a L49 Enchanter for Swift Like the Wind, I'll try it.  <IMG SRC="http://www.neriak.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Sevok Celith'ar<BR>Teir'dal Necromancer, 30th Rank<BR>Xegony<p>[This message has been edited by Sevok Celith'ar (edited March 08, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Omyn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">I haven't really found any spells that make them taunt better.  But any of the buffs from other classes that help increase health will keep the pet in there dealing damage longer.  Periodically my pet will taunt a critter off of someone else, but normally it seems that monsters go for actual players versus pets. <P>Personally, I didn't really think that the last nerf they did to pets was really warranted.  I wish they had simply left it as it was.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Sevok Celith'ar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Omyn:<BR><B>I haven't really found any spells that make them taunt better.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Ya I'm just thinking something like Swift Like the Wind would make them so fast that the MOB would stay on them...<P>As far as the last nerf, no, it wasn't needed.  Bah.<P>------------------<BR>Sevok Celith'ar<BR>Teir'dal Necromancer, 30th Rank<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Gillberg</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Heh funny how we always want pets to hit harder and taunt stuff of us...there's no need for them to taunt at all.  Sevok when you get to 34 you'll understand what I mean.  Hint:  Dooming darkness, send pet, invoke fear, venom of snake, vampric curse, boil blood...(cast all those while you are in the form of bones)...med...if fear wears off (LOVE that update) stand up and cast again...if you need more health suck it back.  Fear keeps the mob away from you and pet...and if you are in a dungeon (which you shouldn't use a pet) you better hope you have a good tank or mem FD...What a good way to solo if you are outside...so just remember if you want your pet to tank better use fear...(a pet is only as good if it stays alive)  If you still have any questions just post something...I'll come back every now and then to check on it...<P>Gillberg Nahcromancer<BR>Da Rathe Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#303070"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Sevok Celith'ar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Gillberg:<BR><B>invoke fear, venom of snake, vampric </B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>If you re-read my post, you'll see that I want the pet to keep stuff off the ROGUE or BARD that I am DUOED with.  I don't solo.  This is a multi-player game, time to get out there and do things with other people.  Besides I play with my RL wife, and her Rogue needs the BACK of the MOB.<P>I know full well how to fear-kite.  It isn't a good option unless you solo.<P><P>------------------<BR>Sevok Celith'ar<BR>Teir'dal Necromancer, 30th Rank<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#202050"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Goast</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">I have used the Fear/Kite with a group before.  <BR>It just isn't efficeint at all.  If you know the pathing, it isn't too bad.  best to have a Bard, or a druid with you though...<P>Distance tends to be key with pets...  Not sure how to help keep its but turned to the rogue  <IMG SRC="http://www.neriak.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
